# OWM-Dataset

## Description
The dataset contains processed intracranial EEG recordings from frontal (LMFG, RMFG) and temporal (LMTG, RMTG) areas of patients performing a load-3 object working memory task.

## Trial data

### LFP recordings
To comply with the .edf format, processed trials (6499 ms each) for every channel were concatenated to a single one-dimensional array. Due to a different number of valid trials across channels, each such array was then padded with 0s on the right ensuring the same data length for all channels within a subject. The total number of concatenated trials per channel and the padding length are recorded in the "_channels.tsv" file for each subject.

### Performance
The sourcedata/ folder contains performance results for every subject. Rows of each table correspond to trials and are in the same order as in the LFP recordings. Columns represent whether the subject selected the presented stimuli during the search period (0 = no, 1 = yes).